Description: Agent for sys-manager: connects a host to a sys-manager server over WebSocket
 and exposes systemd service control, terminal, and config editing.
 Agent for sys-manager — k8s flavor. Same as sys-manager-agent plus a
 compiled-in kube-rs client so the agent can talk to a kube-apiserver
 via in-cluster ServiceAccount or a kubeconfig at $KUBECONFIG. Install
 on hosts that should appear as Kubernetes targets in the dashboard;
 install plain sys-manager-agent everywhere else.

